<includeonly>{{#arraymap:{{Category/effective-subobject-types|category={{{category|}}}}}|,|@@subcat@@|<h3>{{Category/label|category={{PAGENAME:@@subcat@@}}}}</h3>
{{Category/subobject-instances|subcat=@@subcat@@|page={{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}}}}|\n}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Renders subobject sections for a SemanticSchemas category display.

Iterates the effective subobject-type list (including inherited) via
`Category/effective-subobject-types`, emits an `<h3>` heading per type
via `Category/label`, and delegates per-type instance rendering to
`Category/subobject-instances` (which defaults to `Category/subobject-instance`
as the row template — reuses Category/table for each instance).

To customize:
* Change which instances render: pass a different `row-template=`
  argument (requires forking this template)
* Change instance layout: override `Template:Category/subobject-instance`
  globally, OR provide a custom `row-template` to
  `Category/subobject-instances` in your own display code
* Change the heading style: edit this template, or compose your own
  from the primitives on a custom display page

Parameters:
* category - The category name whose subobject types should be rendered
* page     - The parent page whose subobject instances should be listed;
             defaults to {{FULLPAGENAME}}.
</noinclude>
